public int findLongestCycle(int[] edges) {
    int n = edges.length;
    boolean[] visited = new boolean[n];
    int longest_cycle = -1;

    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        if (!visited[i]) {
            int length = 0;
            int node = i;

            while (!visited[node] && edges[node] != -1) {
                visited[node] = true;
                length++;
                node = edges[node];
            }

            if (edges[node] == i) {
                longest_cycle = Math.max(longest_cycle, length);
            }
        }
    }

    return longest_cycle;
}
```

    The algorithm iterates through each node in the graph. For each unvisited node, we start a loop that increases the path length on every iteration until the current node is visited or there is no outgoing edge from the current node. If the next node is equal to the starting node, we found a cycle, which update the longest cycle if it is greater than the current longest cycle.
